headline: Up 25% in the Past 3 Months, Is PayPal Stock a No-Brainer Buy That Can Double in 5 Years?
summary: PayPal (NASDAQ: PYPL) is a leader in the electronic payments niche of the broader financial services industry but hasn't been too kind to investors in recent years.  Does this momentum make the PayPal shares a no-brainer buy that can double in five years?  In the last quarter, Q3 2024, which ended Sept. 30, PayPal processed a whopping $423 billion in total payment volume (TPV), a figure that was up 9% year over year.
